Nurse Hands - I worked as a paramedic from the time I left 'Nam, up until early '80's.  Worked in close proxitiy with Emergency Room, ICU, CCU, Surgical and different floor R.N.'s.  Always kept my eye out for 'Nam vets. Never found any. I later worked with abused and neglected kids up until '92 and so I was still in touch with those at the hospital. Still never came in contact with 'Nam RN's.  About two months ago, I was asked by a RN, whom I knew many years ago working in the ER, if I knew any other 'Nam RN's. She is now a nursing supervisor and, after all these years, I find out that is a vet. Thing is that I remember about twenty four years ago asking her outright if she had been in-country and she denied it vehemently.<br><br>
I understand why she didn't admit to being a vet in those days. I also understand why I hadn't found any others or why they so infrequently surface. For the same reasons that I hadn't seen any platoon medics or any other kind of medics on this site. How many Red Cross Workers have sign their names to any posts here.  Haven't seen one, but again I can understand why.  And I don't think it has anything to do with the raging rapids of testosterone some of these pages are awashed.<br><br>
I counted two 'Nam RN's that I identified on the POV site. Unfortunately for all of us, one signed off as &quot;Just another one&quot;. The other was Nurse Dusty, both contributing to &quot;The Nurses of Viet Nam&quot; thread.  Oh, yea, there are a few of us with &quot;swinging clubs&quot;, who recognize the women vets as I seem to remember that the one who started that particular thread was a male.  Most who had contributed to that thread have been guys paying homage to the women of 'Nam, including myself. It is a shame that there only twelve posts, however. In any case you are right. It also sorrows this vet that more women vets do not come forth. This also include the Red Cross Workers as their contributions were invaluable also.<br><br>
May I make the suggestion that you start a new thread and in doing so, make sure, that, by it's name, that it calls for those that you seek LOUDLY!  My best to you.
